25.1.behavioral_axis: Holds a quiet, principled heart that isn't trying to prove goodness.
25.1.shadow_axis: Collapses when exposed to cruelty; feels the world is corrupt and unsafe.

25.2.behavioral_axis: Radiates unconditional acceptance without effort, makes others feel spiritually safe.
25.2.shadow_axis: Resents being expected to stay pure and forgiving all the time.

25.3.behavioral_axis: Finds authentic compassion by surviving shock, violation, and chaos.
25.3.shadow_axis: Gets cynical, armors the heart, weaponizes 'you can't hurt me anymore.'

25.4.behavioral_axis: Stitches the group back together after harm, through radical non-judgment.
25.4.shadow_axis: Spiritual bypassing to keep the peace and keep access.

25.5.behavioral_axis: Others expect you to cleanse corruption and restore 'heart alignment' for everyone.
25.5.shadow_axis: Blamed as fake, manipulative, or holier-than-thou if healing isn't instant.

25.6.behavioral_axis: Holds a transcendent, unconditional love that isn't personal or transactional.
25.6.shadow_axis: Cold cosmic distance: 'your pain is just part of the lesson, accept it.'

26.1.behavioral_axis: Wants to trade value fairly and protect the tribe's interests.
26.1.shadow_axis: Fear of being seen as a liar, over-defends their honesty.

26.2.behavioral_axis: Can sell, convince, and rearrange agreements without visible force.
26.2.shadow_axis: Pulls away or gets snarky if accused of manipulation.

26.3.behavioral_axis: Finds the line between clever and shady by actually crossing it and recovering.
26.3.shadow_axis: Short-term grifting, burning bridges for quick wins.

26.4.behavioral_axis: Shapes the story so the group keeps leverage and survives materially.
26.4.shadow_axis: Spins reality to secure loyalty and maintain control.

keywords: called in to secure the deal
26.5.behavioral_axis: Others expect you to fix optics, patch reputations, and salvage agreements.
26.5.shadow_axis: Blamed as manipulative propagandist if trust is already gone.

26.6.behavioral_axis: Embodies 'we survive by telling our story on our terms.'
26.6.shadow_axis: Elite spin-doctor energy, weaponized narrative control.

27.1.behavioral_axis: Feels responsible for feeding, supporting, and sustaining the people close in.

27.2.behavioral_axis: Provides what's needed without drama and without needing praise.
27.2.shadow_axis: Withdraws warmth and becomes coldly transactional if taken for granted.

27.3.behavioral_axis: Learns boundaries by overextending and then rebuilding strength.
27.3.shadow_axis: Martyr script: 'after all I've done for you.'

27.4.behavioral_axis: Makes sure everyone in the unit gets fed, seen, and carried.
27.4.shadow_axis: Controls access to support to enforce loyalty.

27.5.behavioral_axis: Others assume you'll keep the whole tribe alive and emotionally fed.
27.5.shadow_axis: Blamed as manipulative or smothering when you ask for reciprocity.

27.6.behavioral_axis: Holds 'care is sacred structure, not optional.'
27.6.shadow_axis: Judges others as unworthy or weak if they can't care like you.

28.1.behavioral_axis: Needs to know the fight actually matters before committing.
28.1.shadow_axis: Existential despair, 'what's the point of any of this.'

28.2.behavioral_axis: Endures hardship with minimal drama when the cause feels worthy.
28.2.shadow_axis: Refuses help, isolates in silent suffering.

28.3.behavioral_axis: Finds true purpose by facing near-collapse and choosing to continue.
28.3.shadow_axis: Reckless risk addiction, flirting with self-destruction.

28.4.behavioral_axis: Rallies allies around 'this is worth the fight, stand with me.'
28.4.shadow_axis: Guilts or pressures people into battles they didn't choose.

28.5.behavioral_axis: Others cast you as the one who can 'stand against the monster.'
28.5.shadow_axis: Crucified if you show weakness or choose self-preservation.

28.6.behavioral_axis: Embodies 'the fight is meaningful because I decided it is.'
28.6.shadow_axis: Detached fatalism, romanticizing suffering as identity.

29.1.behavioral_axis: Wants to anchor in a commitment that feels structurally sound.
29.1.shadow_axis: Fear of overcommitting, stalls instead of answering.

29.2.behavioral_axis: Can stick with something and move it forward just by showing up.
29.2.shadow_axis: Resents being expected to carry everything forever.

29.3.behavioral_axis: Finds honest commitment by surviving bad commitments.
29.3.shadow_axis: Cycle of 'all in' then collapse, seen as unreliable.

29.4.behavioral_axis: Creates shared commitment and morale inside the tribe.
29.4.shadow_axis: Pressures others to stay in situations they've outgrown.

29.5.behavioral_axis: Others expect you to hold the line when everyone else quits.
29.5.shadow_axis: Blamed as controlling or obsessive if you call out quitters.

29.6.behavioral_axis: Embodies that a true yes is a spiritual contract, not casual.
29.6.shadow_axis: Judges others as weak or flaky for changing course.

30.1.shadow_axis: Fear of wanting too much, emotional self-suppression.

30.2.behavioral_axis: Attracts deep emotional experiences just by craving them.
30.2.shadow_axis: Withdraws bitterly when accused of being dramatic or needy.

30.3.behavioral_axis: Finds clarity by surviving emotional intensity spikes and crashes.
30.3.shadow_axis: Chaos chasing, addicted to the high of longing itself.

30.4.behavioral_axis: Lights the group up around 'let's FEEL this fully together.'
30.4.shadow_axis: Stirs drama to keep people hooked and loyal.

30.5.behavioral_axis: Others look to you to voice the deep craving nobody else will admit.
30.5.shadow_axis: Blamed as toxic or manipulative if the desire disrupts comfort.

30.6.behavioral_axis: Embodies that desire is holy fuel, not a flaw.
30.6.shadow_axis: Detached superiority: 'your desires are shallow compared to mine.'

31.1.behavioral_axis: Wants to speak for others only if the position is structurally valid.
31.1.shadow_axis: Insecure about authority, won't speak unless guaranteed status.

31.2.behavioral_axis: People listen when you say 'this is the direction.'
31.2.shadow_axis: Quietly resentful if ignored; disengages instead of adjusting.

keywords: learning to speak for the group
31.3.behavioral_axis: Finds the right leadership voice by messing up in public and adapting.
31.3.shadow_axis: Seen as unreliable mouthpiece, 'can't trust them to represent us.'

31.4.behavioral_axis: Speaks as 'we,' not 'I,' and aligns direction through consensus energy.
31.4.shadow_axis: Plays politics to secure loyalty rather than telling hard truth.

31.5.behavioral_axis: Others expect you to step up, speak for everyone, and stabilize the situation.
31.5.shadow_axis: Blamed as tyrant or manipulator if people don't like the call.

31.6.behavioral_axis: Embodies 'this is the correct direction for us as a people.'
31.6.shadow_axis: Detached rulership, superiority over the 'uninformed masses.'

32.1.behavioral_axis: Wants proof that a thing can actually endure long-term.
32.1.shadow_axis: Anxiety about failure, clings to what's dying out of loyalty.

32.2.behavioral_axis: Can spot which people/ideas are worth investing in over time.
32.2.shadow_axis: Grows bitter if others don't respect that read.

32.3.behavioral_axis: Learns what will survive by backing things that might fail and watching what breaks.
32.3.shadow_axis: Branded unreliable or 'bad judge of character' after visible losses.

32.4.behavioral_axis: Guards long-term stability for the group: 'will this still feed us later?'
32.4.shadow_axis: Uses fears of failure to pressure obedience.

32.5.behavioral_axis: Others assume you know how to prevent collapse and preserve value.
32.5.shadow_axis: Blamed as controlling, territorial, old-guard gatekeeper.

32.6.behavioral_axis: Embodies 'I carry what must not be lost.'
32.6.shadow_axis: Judges evolution as betrayal; refuses necessary change.
